From: Andre Klapper <a9016009@gmx.de>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 22:11:46 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 45/50] XHPASTTreeTestCase: Remove TODO about octal literals
 testcase

Summary:
https://www.php.net/manual/en/migration70.incompatible.php states "Previously, octal literals that contained invalid numbers were silently truncated (0128 was taken as 012). Now, an invalid octal literal will cause a parse error."
https://www.php.net/manual/en/language.types.integer.php defines "octal: 0[oO]?[0-7]+(_[0-7]+)*"

Thus do not test on `080` anymore as it is invalid since PHP 7.

Test Plan: `./bin/arc unit ./src/parser/xhpast/api/__tests__/XHPASTTreeTestCase.php`

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, avivey

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, avivey

Subscribers: tobiaswiese, valerio.bozzolan, Matthew, Cigaryno

Differential Revision: https://we.phorge.it/D26833
---
 src/parser/xhpast/api/__tests__/XHPASTTreeTestCase.php | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/parser/xhpast/api/__tests__/XHPASTTreeTestCase.php b/src/parser/xhpast/api/__tests__/XHPASTTreeTestCase.php
index dfea2c142553..f7e12744fa7e 100644
--- a/src/parser/xhpast/api/__tests__/XHPASTTreeTestCase.php
+++ b/src/parser/xhpast/api/__tests__/XHPASTTreeTestCase.php
@@ -47,8 +47,6 @@ final class XHPASTTreeTestCase extends PhutilTestCase {
 
     // Octal
     $this->assertEval(010, '010');
-    // TODO: this passes on < PHP 7 for some reason but fails on PHP 7 correctly
-    //$this->assertEval(080, '080');  // Invalid!
 
     // Leading 0, but float, not octal.
     $this->assertEval(0.11e1, '0.11e1');
